sap.chart.Chart.constructorDescription:
Constructor for a new Chart. Accepts an object literal mSettings that defines initial property values, aggregated and associated objects as well as event handlers. See {@link sap.ui.base.ManagedObject#constructor} for a general description of the syntax of the settings object. The supported settings are:
  • Properties
    • {@link #getChartType chartType} : string (default: bar)
    • {@link #getUiConfig uiConfig} : object
    • {@link #getVisibleDimensions visibleDimensions} : string[] (default: [])
    • {@link #getInResultDimensions inResultDimensions} : string[] (default: [])
    • {@link #getVisibleMeasures visibleMeasures} : string[] (default: [])
    • {@link #getVizProperties vizProperties} : object
    • {@link #getVizScales vizScales} : object[]
    • {@link #getIsAnalytical isAnalytical} : boolean
    • {@link #getSelectionBehavior selectionBehavior} : string (default: DATAPOINT)
    • {@link #getSelectionMode selectionMode} : string (default: sap.chart.SelectionMode.Multi)
    • {@link #getEnablePagination enablePagination} : boolean (default: false)
  • Aggregations
    • {@link #getData data} : sap.ui.core.Element[]
    • {@link #getDimensions dimensions} : sap.chart.data.Dimension[]
    • {@link #getMeasures measures} : sap.chart.data.Measure[]
  • Events
    • {@link #event:drilledDown drilledDown} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:drilledUp drilledUp} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:renderComplete renderComplete} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:selectData selectData} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:deselectData deselectData} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
In addition, all settings applicable to the base type {@link sap.viz.ui5.controls.common.BaseControl#constructor sap.viz.ui5.controls.common.BaseControl} can be used as well.

unitBinding.description:
Unit for the measure, a pointer using the binding syntax to some field containing the unit.
Value of the given field from the same data record will be displayed after formatted measure value in data label, tooltip and chart popover.
NOTE: If the unit field is not set as visible dimension in chart, or more than one unit value exists 
for any visible dimension value combination, they will be rendered in the chart resulting different chart layout.

role.description:
How values of measure will be rendered in the chart. Possible role values are "axis1", "axis2", "axis3", and "axis4".
The default is "axis1".
They correspond to the well-known concepts of axis identifiers in the Cartesian coordinate system, e.g. a Y-axis in a bar/column/line chart, an X- and a Y-axis in a scatter chart, or two Y-axes in bar charts, and an optional third axis for the weight/size/intensity/temperature of a data point.

LayoutData classes are typed classes and must match the embedding Layout.
See VariantLayoutData for aggregating multiple alternative LayoutData instances to a single Element.
layoutData.helpDescription:
Defines the layout constraints for this control when it is used inside a Layout.
LayoutData classes are typed classes and must match the embedding Layout.
See VariantLayoutData for aggregating multiple alternative LayoutData instances to a single Element.

tooltip.description:
The tooltip that should be shown for this Element.

Can either be an instance of a TooltipBase subclass or a simple string.
tooltip.helpDescription:
The tooltip that should be shown for this Element.

Can either be an instance of a TooltipBase subclass or a simple string.

customData.description: Custom Data, a data structure like a map containing arbitrary key value pairs.
customData.helpDescription: Custom Data, a data structure like a map containing arbitrary key value pairs.

dependents.description: Dependents are not rendered, but their databinding context and lifecycle are bound to the aggregating Element.
dependents.helpDescription: Dependents are not rendered, but their databinding context and lifecycle are bound to the aggregating Element.

textFormatter.description:
Function returning a formatted text for a Dimension key value that will be used for axis labelling. If specified, this property takes precedence over the "textProperty" property of the Dimension.
Dimension key value and the corresponding text will be passed to the supplied function as parameters.
textFormatter.helpDescription:
Function returning a formatted text for a Dimension key value that will be used for axis labelling. If specified, this property takes precedence over the "textProperty" property of the Dimension.
Dimension key value and the corresponding text will be passed to the supplied function as parameters.

displayText.description: Whether a text is displayed. If the "textProperty" property has not been specified, it will be derived from the metadata.
displayText.helpDescription: Whether a text is displayed. If the "textProperty" property has not been specified, it will be derived from the metadata.

models.description: A map of model instances to which the object should be attached, keyed by the model names. Each entry with key k in this object has the same effect as a call to this.setModel(models[k], k). For the default model, String(undefined) must be used as key. Instead of a map, a single model instance can be given which will be set as default model.

textProperty.description: Text for a Dimension key value, typically by a pointer using the binding syntax to some property containing the text.
textProperty.helpDescription: Text for a Dimension key value, typically by a pointer using the binding syntax to some property containing the text.

role.description:
How the Dimension will influence the chart layout. Possible values are "category" or "series".
The default is "category".
NOTE: Has no effect if the Dimension is used as inResultDimensions by Chart
role.helpDescription:
How the Dimension will influence the chart layout. Possible values are "category" or "series".
The default is "category".
NOTE: Has no effect if the Dimension is used as inResultDimensions by Chart

objectBindings.description: A map of binding paths keyed by the corresponding model name. Each entry with key k in this object has the same effect as a call to this.bindObject(objectBindings[k], k);. For the default model, String(undefined) must be used as key. Instead of a map, a single binding path can be given which will be bound for the default model.

name.description: Property in the "data" model holding the (always unique) Dimension key.
name.helpDescription: Property in the "data" model holding the (always unique) Dimension key.

label.description: Label for the Dimension, either as a string literal or by a pointer using the binding syntax to some property containing the label.
label.helpDescription: Label for the Dimension, either as a string literal or by a pointer using the binding syntax to some property containing the label.

id.description:
Unique ID of this instance.

If not given, a so called autoID will be generated by the framework.
AutoIDs use a unique prefix that must not be used for IDs that the application (or other code) creates.
It can be configured by using option 'autoIDPrefix', see {@link sap.ui.core.Configuration}.

timeUnit.description: Detailed unit infomation of TimeDimension. Please refer to {@link sap.chart.TimeUnitType TimeUnitType}.
timeUnit.helpDescription: Detailed unit infomation of TimeDimension. Please refer to {@link sap.chart.TimeUnitType TimeUnitType}.

bindingContexts.description: A map of {@link sap.ui.model.Context} instances keyed by their model name. Each entry with key k in this object has the same effect as a call to this.setBindingContext(bindingContexts[k], k). For the default model, String(undefined) must be used as key. Instead of a map, a single context can be given which will be set for the default model.

formatError.name: formatError
formatError.description:
Fired when a new value for a bound property should have been propagated from the model,
but formatting the value failed with an exception.
formatError.helpDescription:
Fired when a new value for a bound property should have been propagated from the model,
but formatting the value failed with an exception.
formatError.type: fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]

selectData.name: selectData
selectData.description: Event fires when certain data point(s) is(are) selected, data context of selected item(s) would be passed in.
selectData.type: fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]

parseError.name: parseError
parseError.description:
Fired when a new value for a bound property should have been propagated to the model,
but parsing the value failed with an exception.
parseError.helpDescription:
Fired when a new value for a bound property should have been propagated to the model,
but parsing the value failed with an exception.
parseError.type: fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]

validationSuccess.name: validationSuccess
validationSuccess.description:
Fired after a new value for a bound property has been propagated to the model.
Only fired, when the binding uses a data type.
validationSuccess.helpDescription:
Fired after a new value for a bound property has been propagated to the model.
Only fired, when the binding uses a data type.
validationSuccess.type: fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]

modelContextChange.name: modelContextChange
modelContextChange.description: Fired when models or contexts are changed on this object (either by calling setModel/setBindingContext or due to propagation)
modelContextChange.helpDescription: Fired when models or contexts are changed on this object (either by calling setModel/setBindingContext or due to propagation)
modelContextChange.type: fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]

validationError.name: validationError
validationError.description:
Fired when a new value for a bound property should have been propagated to the model,
but validating the value failed with an exception.
validationError.helpDescription:
Fired when a new value for a bound property should have been propagated to the model,
but validating the value failed with an exception.
validationError.type: fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
